=== Dialogue Wordpress Plugin ===
Contributors: Lincoln Sousa, Fabrício Soares
Tags: public participation, Legislation, non-linear narratives
Tested with: 2.9.2

A plugin for displaying comments per paragraph.

== Description ==

Plugin that allows public and collaborative participation on
the process of constructing text, developed by the Brazilian
Ministry of Culture (Ministério da Cultura) for supporting
the construction of a democratic debate evolving laws.

== Installation ==

1. Upload the `dialogue` folder to the `/wp-content/plugins/`
directory
1. Activate the plugin through the 'Plugins' menu in
WordPress or by using the link provided by the plugin installer.

== Usage ==

1. Install.
2. Activate.
3. Enable dialogue on the post. Using the option "Enable dialogue
   in this post"
4. Mark the commentable areas with the [commentable][/commentable]
See the example:

  [commentable id="paragraph1"]
  faucibus. Vestibulum pretium aliquet arcu, et lobortis massa varius
  in. Ut porta mollis lorem et scelerisque. Fusce non ipsum at lorem
  laoreet pulvinar. Quisque lacus risus, accumsan hendrerit ultrices
  ut, congue vitae nisl. Pellentesque facilisis, magna sed
  ullamcorper rutrum, lectus lectus egestas odio, consequat mollis
  tellus est sed sem. Ut ligula elit, laoreet vel viverra nec,
  interdum dignissim est.
  [/commentable]

Be careful with the id property. It is used to associate a comment
with something we call a "paragraph". You can use any kind of text
in this field but you have to make sure you will fill it.
